com.ibm.team.repository.client.util

Interface IPropertyChangeEvent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEvent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PropertyChangeEvent

    public interface IPropertyChangeEvent
extends IEvent
    A description of a property change that has occurred for some object and originated from some event source.

    Typically an event source that fires property change events, will declare property constants in its interface and provide documentation of which API calls will cause those properties to change. Listeners for property change events will be registered by passing the property constant as a category argument when calling IEventSource#addGenericListener.

    Since:
    0.5

        java.lang.Object getOldValue()
        Returns the value of the object's property before the change occurred. For a list-based property, this represents a value, or a list of values, removed from the list. For a move, this represents the old position of the moved value.
